sql:
SELECT product_description
FROM ovens
WHERE max_temperature > 850;

SELECT oven_id, max_temperature, fuel_type
FROM ovens
ORDER BY max_temperature DESC;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS pending_customizations
FROM customizations
WHERE status = 'Pending';

SELECT oven_id, quantity_available
FROM inventory
WHERE quantity_available = (SELECT MAX(quantity_available) FROM inventory);

SELECT max_temperature
FROM ovens
ORDER BY max_temperature DESC;

SELECT product_description
FROM ovens
WHERE oven_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Assume that "pizza oven models" can encompass various types and sizes of ovens designed for cooking pizzas; 
- "Specifications" include internal dimensions, hearth surface area, dome shape, vault height, door height, door width, flue width, foundation dimensions, pizza capacity, material, fuel type, maximum temperature, cool-down time, weight, product image, product description, and warranty period; 
- "Sales history" refers to the total quantity sold and total revenue generated by each oven model; 
- "Current inventory status" covers the total quantity available, total quantity on order, last restocked date, next restock date, and minimum stock level for each oven model; 
- "Customization requests" include the total number of requests, completed customizations, and pending customizations for each oven model; 
- "Cumulative revenue" is the running total of revenue from the sales of the ovens.
